HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 44
By Keisling
A RESOLUTION to commend and congratulate Nate Adams of
Clay County High School upon being named a
runner-up for the 2024 Tennessee Titans Mr.
Football Award for Division I, Class A.
WHEREAS, we are pleased to recognize and commend those successful high school
athletes who, through their magnificent exploits, bring honor to Tennessee and serve as
exceptional ambassadors of this State; and
WHEREAS, one such estimable individual is Nate Adams of Clay County High School,
an athlete of extraordinary talent, skill, and dedication, who has proven himself a formidable
competitor on the football field; and
WHEREAS, an exceptional quarterback, Nate Adams was recently named a runner-up
for the prestigious Tennessee Titans Mr. Football Award for TSSAA Division I, Class A, in
recognition of his excellence on the gridiron for Clay County High School; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Adams holds virtually all passing records at Clay County High School
after totaling 7,586 yards and eighty-nine touchdowns in his career and another program record
with thirty-one defensive interceptions; his outstanding performance on the gridiron is a
testament to his dedication and passion for the sport; and
WHEREAS, Nate Adams epitomizes all that is good in today's student athlete, as he has
achieved a high level of success in sports while evincing great character both on and off the
field; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Adams's notable achievement is a source of great pride for his family,
his community, and his school, and it is appropriate that we recognize this accomplished
athlete; now, therefore;
